snippet.textDisplay:
Worked great from me. Comments specific to this composition (and any CS composition for that matter) are nothing outside the norm considering we all come from differing cultures, geographic areas and have different tastes and points of reference.  We each have our unique connection to the compositions and it sure sucks when intolerance creeps in with 
someone mocking and disrespecting another's preference/comment.  Somebody dissed the composition for straying to far from his/her definition of how Sufi poetry and music needs to be rendered.  Coke Studio's Sufi fusion renditions are what made me fall in love with whatever little I know and understand about Sufism.  This new fusion-esque packaging of Sufi poetry and music works great in my personal opinion considering it appeals to a broader audience and generates an extended fan base.  The purists would still call this bastardization............well, so be it.  They will forever spew hate, anger and intolerance.....values that contradict core Sufi principles of divinity, love, free soulfulness in the first place. This is like a 
microcosm of the world we live in today.

Thank you Coke Studio from adding this dimension to my life.  Enough said..............peace out.
